##Wuhan Epidemic Area Dictation: These 3 habits, the same can not be less

Micro-signal Zhenghedao

Features introduced by Zhenghe Island, a high-end social networking platform focused on entrepreneurs.

During the special period, Wuhan has become a city where people all over the country are concerned and pray for good fortune. What was the real life of the people of Wuhan after the city closure?

Zhenghe island has launched a special column, "Ye Qing: My n day in Wuhan Epidemic Area" , since January 26. Ye Qing, a resident of Wuhan for 40 years, is a scholar and official. For a period of time, he would write down his own experiences and observations of Wuhan, and he would go out to the streets and supermarkets to get first-hand information.

This will be a valuable piece of historical material. Thanks to him, we can feel the Wuhan epidemic more vividly. Let's Cheer for Wuhan Together!

Ye Qing, a professor at Zhongnan University of Economics and Law and deputy director of the Hubei Provincial Bureau of Statistics, is next door to blue island

Source: Zhenghe Island (ID: Zhenghedao)

There's an improvement in the numbers

January 28, the fourth day of the first lunar month, Wuhan Sunny.

From October 28th to 24th, 31 provinces, autonomous regions and municipalities reported 1,459 new confirmed cases, 263 new severe cases, 26 new deaths, 25 new cases in Hubei Province, 1 new case in Henan Province, and 43 new cured cases, there were 3,248 new suspected cases, including one in Tibet.

As of 2400 hours on January 28, the National Health Commission had received 5974 confirmed cases from 31 provinces, autonomous regions and municipalities, with 1239 severe cases, 132 deaths and 103 cured cases. There are 9,239 suspected cases.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
On the 28th, there was a major turning point in Wuhan, which saw a sharp drop in new cases. This can not but be said to be the result of strong control.

The medical power of Wuhan has been greatly enhanced

Vice Premier Sun Chunlan led a central guidance team to carry out epidemic prevention and control work in Hubei on March 28. The Steering Group held successive meetings to hear reports on the work of epidemic prevention and control in Hubei Province, and to study and guide the further work of epidemic prevention and control, patient treatment, epidemiological investigation, publicity and public opinion guidance. It is conceivable that the State Council's instructions to Wuhan, Hubei, will be more and more integrated with the actual situation in Wuhan.

Our greatest concern, the lack of medical care, has been alleviated. As of the 27th, a total of 30 medical teams, a total of 4,130 medical staff arrived in Hubei to start work. Thirteen more medical teams arrived on the 28th, with a total of 1,800 people.

As of the evening of January 28, nearly 6,000 medical teams from all over the country had been sent to Hubei to support the epidemic. Wuhan, Hubei Province has become the most adequate area for medical treatment. In this way, we Hubei people can rest assured.

Our paramedics are the most beautiful.

A group of 31 nurses at the Wuhan Union Hospital had their long hair cut to make it easier for them to wear protective clothing and care for patients.

A "bald nurse" took a Selfie that went viral on social media Thursday. Many people left messages expressing their admiration for their professionalism and positive and brave personality.

The girl was dressed as a nurse in the East Hospital of Wuhan University People's Hospital, and her name was listed on her name tag as Shan Xia. The 29-year-old is an experienced nurse in neurology and a mother of two.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
We often say, "the Spring River Warm Duck Prophet. ". In fact, doctors are the most sensitive to the outbreak.

Before the Zhong Nanshan spoke, the doctor in Wuhan alerted a nearby school about Lu Xiaohong, director of the Department of gastroenterology at Wuhan's Fifth Hospital, according to an article published by China Youth Daily.

On January 2,2020, she suggested setting up a fever clinic

Love flows to Wuhan like a tide

According to "China Economic Weekly" reporter incomplete statistics, as of January 28 morning, there have been nearly 200 enterprises emergency relief, donations, donations, online epidemic service platform. At present, the total amount of donations exceeds 5 billion, 20 enterprises have donated more than 100 million.

Alibaba 1 billion, tencent 300 million, Baidu 300 million, Meituan 200 million, Evergrande 200 million, China merchants 200 million, Geely 200 million, gREE 100 million, Kuaishou 100 million, Feihe 100 million, country garden 100 million, Vanke 100 million, Rongchuang 110 million, good future 100 million, CTRIP 100 million, Yili 100 million, the United States 100 million, 100 million brand gold light group 100 million.

Among them, about 40 real estate enterprises have confirmed to donate funds and materials to Wuhan, with a total donation amount of nearly 900 million yuan. Evergrande, SUNAC, Country Garden and Vanke have donated a total of 510 million yuan, accounting for more than half of the total amount donated by housing enterprises.

Wuhan Alumni Enterprise SUNAC China was the first company to announce a donation to Wuhan. On the evening of the 23rd, SUNAC China announced a donation of 10 million yuan to the Wuhan Red Cross, and on the 25th, SUNAC Public Welfare Foundation announced another donation of 100 million yuan to the Wuhan Charity Federation.

In order to improve the transparency of the use of donations and reassure donors, Red Cross societies at all levels and charity associations will announce the use of donations and gifts as soon as possible.

I am the supervisor of Hubei Provincial Charity Association, and I am particularly concerned about this.

As of 18:00 on the 27th, the Hubei Charity Federation had received 408 million yuan in donations from the public. On the 28th, all the donations have been transferred to charity associations all over the province.

Drive around listening to the news, kill two birds with one stone

On the afternoon of the 28th, I went out once again to feel the scarcity of people and vehicles in Wuhan, it is hard to avoid heartache. However, if we do not respect the laws of nature, do not do a good job of environmental sanitation, such a scenario may occur in the future.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Attention, the 12 words on the screen are "exit route closed, please understand and support. ". At this moment, to the "closed city" on the sixth day, there should be no one in Wuhan will object to it.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
I passed a gas station. It was empty. I had to fill it up. The gas man said that on the 29th day of the 12th month, the first day of the "closure of the city" , the gas cars lined up in a convoy, the 30th day of the 12th month was less. There's less now. There's less to do.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
This Spring Festival, let a lot of travel, tourism, entertainment-related industries diving. There's no way around it.

My habit is to listen to the radio driving, first-hand information, to avoid wasting this period of time driving. Of course, don't copy me if you're bad. At work, I go out at 6:30, arrive at the office in half an hour, it takes me an hour to get home from work. Thus, I have an hour and a half a day to listen to the radio, timely economic information.

As I drove, I watched the deserted streets and listened to the CCTV news.

CCTV news focused on the situation of the major hospitals in Wuhan, the reporters and medical staff dialogue is very vivid. This is much better than watching Wechat, the eyes will not be so uncomfortable.

I call it 'the leaf reading method'  Three listening.

Three: read paper books, read e-books, read "breakfast of Finance and Economics" ("Economic Daily" wechat public account) .

Three listen: Lazy Listen to the book, drive to listen to the news, all kinds of reading club 25 minutes "a book a day. ".

Now, I use "wechat reading" more. This kind of reading software can see, can listen, can also see while listening, so that reading becomes a kind of enjoyment. Can also protect the eyes, eyes tired, close your eyes to listen. Therefore, a book with listening and reading, will soon read.

Online and remote will eventually become a habit

When does Wuhan's big middle and Primary Schools Start School? How do I get to class? Is a concern for many families.

The Wuhan Education Bureau (EDB) announced on its website on 28th that:

The opening time of municipal schools at all levels (including primary and secondary schools, kindergartens, secondary vocational schools, municipal colleges and social training institutions) will be extended in the spring of 2020. Starting from February 1, the third year of Senior High School will be organized to carry out online teaching. Starting from February 10, all district education bureaus will organize primary and secondary schools and secondary vocational schools under their jurisdiction to carry out online course teaching according to the teaching plan.

Schools can do this, and businesses can work remotely.

Tencent announced that it will start working from home on February 1 and February 3-7, tentatively scheduled to return to work on February 10(January 17) .

Bytedance recommends that employees in mainland China stay where they are until Feb. 9(inclusive) . Staff currently away from their place of work start telecommuting on 31 January and return to their place of work from 10 to 13 February, then telecommuting for 14 days in isolation at home and travel to the office after confirmation of absence of symptoms; for extended periods of return, employees who work from home but do not have a computer can apply, and the company will courier IT inventory computers.

On the 28th, Baidu announced to its employees that it will start working from home on February 3-7, and will return to work on February 10(January 17) . At this point, BAT three Internet giants all start after the Spring Festival at Home Office mechanism.

We have been advocating online teaching, telecommuting, telemedicine, and so on, perhaps in this year's "new pneumonia" under the promotion, will accelerate the pace of popularization. I guess I'll just have to tell myself that.

No one gets left behind

Yesterday's Article "Wuhan Epidemic Area Dictation: Do not let go of the supermarket! " After the release, a netizen left a message: The proposal to increase the supermarket pay the mouth. This is OK, can execute flexible window, the person is much increase toll clerk, much open toll hole. But I think it's more important to pay your own way in the supermarket. When I saw some people in line at the supermarket, I switched to paying in the self-service area.

It is a good suggestion to promote supermarket self-service payment.

According to yesterday's article, you can't lose your gloves. There's a lot to talk about today.

Laurie Garrett is a well-known American journalist, the first person to win three prestigious Journalism Awards (The Peabody Award, the George and the Pulitzer) , and a senior fellow in global health at the Council on Foreign Relations. Gloves are more important than masks, she says!

When you leave home, put on gloves, winter gloves or outdoor gloves, and don't take them off in any public places, including subways and buses, she said.

Do not touch your face or eyes with your hand in certain social situations, such as shaking hands or eating, and do not let your hand touch your face, no matter how itchy. Before putting the gloves back on, wash your hands carefully with warm water and soap, Rub your fingers well, and then put on the gloves.

I was inspired to read this article. The Chinese hand-me-down ceremony is very hygienic.

Things bought in supermarkets do not need to be sterilized, and there is not much chance that items in the supermarket will be contaminated by patients'saliva, Feng Zijian, deputy director of the Chinese Center for Disease Control and Prevention, told CCTV on the evening of the 28th. We can't sterilize everything. The most important thing is to wash your hands.

No matter how we put it, we must always remember: wear gloves, wear masks, wash hands frequently, these three things can not be less, to become the Chinese nation's permanent habits. Remember the "sars" era we also do this, but as time goes by, we gradually forget.

Our families

Our "grandma" has a new move. One is to send red envelopes on the WECHAT group from time to time, and you can almost hear the laughter from families all over the world. The other is to ask each family to sing a song together, and then connect them together. The third is to take photos of each family's delicious food, but through the screen, it's just too much to hope for.

We use the word "community" A lot. I think of a community as a group of people who are not related by blood or by executive order, but who speak the same language and think alike.

The teacher-student relationship is one such community.

In fact, since I joined Jungho last September, I've found this community in the corporate world. For example, is a book cabinet established by the island is such.

Founded in 2004, the school has branches in Beijing, Nanchang, Changsha, Ganzhou, Jiujiang and Berlin, Germany. As of July 2018, there were 185 teaching bases and more than 50,000 students.

What is surprising is not this, but the idea of "business as a family" .

The book's partners have built a family business, not a family business, and have been together for generations to come, and have identified sixteen generations of descendants: only Dejia, always bright. Be Modest and create the world with Benevolence, righteousness and broadness.

For example, the chairman's daughter is called "Li Weiqing" . Wei Qing, that is, the word "Wei" generation GE baby. It is also a community that is not related by blood but rather by blood.

Conclusion

In this different Spring Festival, the sunshine is more and more beautiful, the temperature is higher and higher, the virus will be less and less.

In the face of an increasingly powerful medical force, patients are more and more sure to get treatment, and people's fear will be lower and lower.

Today, fewer people are newly infected in Wuhan; tomorrow, Fewer People will die. Let us pray!

Think about embedding the Internet into people's work and life, and hopefully good hygiene will always be with you. A country is only as strong as its people.
